  • Method Details

    • equals

      public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object obj)
      this is a simple overridden equals() method that will be used, in conjunction with a hashCode(), to see if two rats are the same two rats. These Rats will said to be the same if they are the same object OR if two rats have the same age if this returns true and the hashcode is the same for both Rats, then both rats will NOT BE added
      Overrides:
      equals in class java.lang.Object

    • hashCode

      public int hashCode()
      This is a overridden() method that will be used, in conjunction with equals() method, to see if two rats are deemed to be the same two rats. if two Rats have the same age, they will have the same HashCode number, so two Rats of the same age will NOT be added to the set

      hashCode in class java.lang.Object
